President Obama has announced his intention to nominate Matthew Olsen as the Director of the National Counterterrorism Center (NCTC). If confirmed, Olsen will be responsible for integrating intelligence and sharing information with agencies across the federal government to protect Americans from terrorist threats. Currently serving as the General Counsel for the National Security Agency (NSA), Olsen has a distinguished record of service in the intelligence community. He has also held various positions in the Department of Justice, including supervising national security and criminal matters. Olsen is a graduate of Harvard Law School and the University of Virginia, and he is an adjunct professor of law at Georgetown University.